<br>
Everyone is entitled to their opinion, and everyone is entitled to post such an opinion on the web.  Some of the points that are made are valid.<br>
<br>
What I do not agree with are when people report things that aren't right.  I think the one response clears up several of those for this article, but regardless of what color your glasses are, at least get the facts right.<br>
<br>
Other than that, it's an opinion based on a certain perspective.  It doesn't make it right, but it doesn't make it wrong. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukorraisashadowsgate.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Korraisa Shadowsgate</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Bonecollecter</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/19/01 6:18:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=57.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I'll let you guys judge for yourselves...</span><hr size=1> OoC: Agreed, some points they made were valid.  But isn't taking your aggression out on some computerised monster, while knowing it's a game, better than throwing things or letting it bottle up in one's own self.  The one other point that strikes me as stupid to even mention is the profanity.  I would have to point out what they get away with on television.  Most of the time when someone starts spewing profanity at someone or the entire zone via /auction, /shout, /ooc...everyone jumps on him or jumps over to /petition and he gets booted.  I think most of us here on Firiona Vie are more civilised than we are in real life.  Because we try to make an effort; sometimes in real life it's NOT worth it. <p><img src="http://www.wynd-haven.com/sigtempt.jpg">
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujantisconstanceeorle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jantis ConstanceEorle</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moo</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/19/01 6:58:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=57.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.warghoul.com/images/CoSS/jantis_head_ez.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I'll let you guys judge for yourselves...</span><hr size=1> Anything said about the EQ chat channels can be said about any chat group on the internet.  At least Verant has two mechanisms in place to deal with it, which I did not see them mention - petition (cursing in a public channel is grounds for warning, etc) and the chat filter.  I have several friends that use the foul language filter, although some that curse feel the foul language filter somehow makes it ok to curse in a public forum.  I might suggest they read the rules of conduct.<br>
<br>
At the same time, I've never seen it a valid excuse to say that it's ok to do something in one area just because they do worse elsewhere.  To say the get away with worse language on television doesn't justify doing something 'a little less bad' in EverQuest.  It isn't a specific matter of cursing, it is all a matter of respect for others.<br>
<br>
Personally, I feel that Verant does a commendable job in the area of cursing compared to other on-line environments.  <br>
<br>
I've never believed that killing creatures on a screen is a tension reliever.  Nor have I ever witnissed someone go into EverQuest angry and come out relaxed after a night of killing.  I'm not saying there aren't folks out there that do, but most of the people I know log out in a worse mood if anything, unless maybe they spent the night fishing or maybe doing quests.  EverQuest can easily cause as much tension as it relieves, though that isn't their point anyway.  Their point is aggressive encouragement, which is a matter of becoming inductive to solving problems by violent reaction and by becoming numb to seeing violence as a way to solve problems.<br>
<br>
The issue I have with trying to take either side of this to some extreme is because there is no simple answer to any of it.  There are people (not just kids, but adults too) that respond to violence in a way that causes them to mimic it in other ways in their lives.  They truly get worse playing games like this, becoming jerks and angry all the time.  There are just as many people that come in from work or school upset and can go kill a few monsters and feel better about themselves.<br>
<br>
There is no single answer because there is no single reaction.  That's why it's really a moot point, and if you find yourself (or see your spouse or your child) reacting negatively to the game, you should encourage them to find another outlet and take a break (maybe even permanent) from the game.  The biggest problem is people don't make the change, and they just get sucked deeper and deeper into their depression or their anger or whatever negative feelings they have.<br>
<br>
It's the same reason some people can play D&amp;D and some people freak out.  It's why some people can lead normal lives and listen to heavy metal, and others hear the demons whispering for them to go kill.  It's a combination of things that foster feelings and the person being open and receptive to those feelings.<br>
<br>
ok... *turns over his sign to say &quot;The Doctor is Out&quot;*... I'm tired of rambling, hehe. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#A62A2A>- </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4>The Soapbox</a> <font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href="http://www.firionavie.org/">Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.6.8<br>Copyright ©1999-2001 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  